# Template Validation Checklist (V2)

Read when: validating that template application is complete and compliant.
Skip when: never.

## Core Presence
- [ ] `AI_AGENT.md` exists and is used as mandatory startup file
- [ ] `docs/AI_MEMORY.md` exists
- [ ] `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md` exists
- [ ] `docs/TECH_STACK.md` exists
- [ ] `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` exists
- [ ] `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` exists
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` exists with `Unreleased`
- [ ] `.github/workflows/ci.yml` exists
- [ ] `docs/TEMPLATE_INDEX.yaml` exists and matches applied files
- [ ] If `AI_OPERATING_CONTRACT.md` exists, it does not define separate rules

## Placeholder Integrity
- [ ] No unresolved placeholders like `[PROJECT_NAME]`, `[VERIFY_COMMAND]`
- [ ] All commands execute in target environment
- [ ] Tier is selected with rationale

## Quality Gate Integrity
- [ ] Verify gate runs and passes
- [ ] Smoke command runs
- [ ] At least one targeted workflow test exists
- [ ] Workflow-to-test matrix is populated

## Tier Compliance
- [ ] Tier A advanced controls are implemented or marked `N/A` with rationale
- [ ] Tier B advanced controls are implemented where applicable
- [ ] Tier C all advanced controls are implemented

## Optional Add-ons
- [ ] `README.md` present and aligned to project quickstart/docs
- [ ] `.gitignore` present and excludes secrets/runtime artifacts
- [ ] `CONTRIBUTING.md` present when collaboration is expected
- [ ] `LICENSE` present when licensing should be explicit
- [ ] PR and issue templates present when repo uses issue/PR workflow
- [ ] Optional CI variant selected if runtime-specific template is preferred
- [ ] Multi-app blueprint used when hosting multiple apps
- [ ] Local compose template used when compose runtime is required
- [ ] Optional first-session prompt used only if preferred
- [ ] ADR template used when architecture decisions need explicit records
